openobserver-description =
    OpenObserve is a cloud-native, Rust-based observability platform for logs, metrics,
    traces, and dashboards.

    It is a high-performance, low-storage-cost alternative to Elasticsearch and Grafana
    stacks. OpenObserve ingests data via OpenTelemetry, supports SQL queries, and provides
    built-in dashboards, alerts, and scheduled reports. It can be combined with the
    otel-collector for a complete observability pipeline.

openobserver-features =
    - Logs, metrics, and distributed traces in one platform
    - OpenTelemetry-native ingestion
    - SQL query engine for ad-hoc analysis
    - Built-in dashboards and visualizations
    - Alerts and scheduled reports
    - 140x lower storage cost compared to Elasticsearch
    - Written in Rust — low resource footprint
    - S3-compatible object storage for data
